[1/10] P5 English EOY Nanyang 2025 — Q1  Primary 5  (13.6s)
============================================================
STEM: Jenny was worried about the upcoming test ___ she did not revise enough.
  (1) if
  (2) as
  (3) unless
  (4) therefore
ANSWER: 2

ELABORATION (584 chars):
This question tests **subordinating conjunctions of reason**, which connect a situation to its cause. 

Option **(2)** is correct because "as" means "because." It correctly explains the reason why Jenny was worried (she did not revise enough).

- Option **(1)** fails because "if" creates a **conditional sentence**, but her lack of revision is a fact, not a possibility.
- Option **(3)** fails because "unless" means "except if," creating an illogical **negative condition**.
- Option **(4)** fails because "therefore" is a **conjunctive adverb** used to show a result, not a reason.

